Description: Body sherd of Corinthian black-figured pottery open vessel, possibly a kylix; interior glazed (fired red to brown); exterior: from top, black-figure decoration consisting pair of human feet with incised pin wheel rosette as filling ornament between each foot; two narrow bands; black-figure animal procession (part of head, wings, back and tail feathers of bird remaining) to left.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GB.082) (Phase 1)
